<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF496AF6F7E397561712BAFC" pageId="178" pageNumber="940" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FF496AF6F7E397561712BAFC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398773" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398773/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="940" targetBox="[1464,2056,282,696]" targetPageId="178">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF496AF6F7E397561712BAFC" blockId="178.[2079,2673,271,698]" pageId="178" pageNumber="940">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF496AF6F7E3975616CFBA02" bold="true" box="[2079,2255,271,304]" pageId="178" pageNumber="940">Distribution.</emphasis>
Widely distributed in Neotropics, from S Veracruz in Mexico, S through Central and South America to 
